  "text": "The HTTP filter chain extension mechanism in envoyproxy/envoy spans three key layers:\n\n1. **Filter Factory Registry**: `envoy/server/filter_config.h` defines `NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory` and `HttpFilterConfigFactoryBase` \u2014 the interfaces each HTTP filter implements and registers via `Registry::FactoryRegistry` (defined in `envoy/registry/registry.h`). Filters register via `REGISTER_FACTORY()` macro. `source/common/filter/config_discovery_impl.h` provides ECDS (dynamic filter config) via `HttpFilterConfigProviderManagerImpl`.\n\n2. **Filter Context & Interfaces**: `envoy/http/filter_factory.h` defines the core abstractions: `FilterFactoryCb` (the factory callback lambda), `FilterContext` (config name metadata), `FilterChainManager` (sink for filter creation), `FilterChainFactory` (creates filter chain per-stream), and `FilterChainOptions`. `envoy/http/filter.h` defines `StreamDecoderFilter`, `StreamEncoderFilter`, `StreamFilter`, and `FilterChainFactoryCallbacks` (the callbacks used to add filters to the chain).\n\n3. **Per-Request Filter Chain Execution**: `source/common/http/filter_manager.h` and `.cc` contain `FilterManager` (implements `FilterChainManager`, drives decode/encode through filter chains via `ActiveStreamDecoderFilter`/`ActiveStreamEncoderFilter` wrappers). `source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.h` and `.cc` contain `FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories()` and the `FilterChainHelper` template that builds filter factory lists from config. `source/common/http/conn_manager_impl.h` and `.cc` contain `ConnectionManagerImpl` and its `ActiveStream` which owns the `DownstreamFilterManager` and triggers `createFilterChain()` on new requests.",
